cjnIpxRipEnabled.name: cjnIpxRipEnabled
cjnIpxRipEnabled.description: Enable / Disable IPX RIP on this system.

cjnIpxRipFilterTable.name: cjnIpxRipFilterTable
cjnIpxRipFilterTable.description: A list of Cajun IPX RIP filters.

cjnIpxRipFilterEntry.name: cjnIpxRipFilterEntry
cjnIpxRipFilterEntry.description: A Cajun IPX RIP filter instance.

cjnIpxRipFilterPrec.name: cjnIpxRipFilterPrec
cjnIpxRipFilterPrec.description: The precedence of this RIP filter. The precedence is relative to other RIP filters on the same interface.

cjnIpxRipFilterRowStatus.name: cjnIpxRipFilterRowStatus
cjnIpxRipFilterRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

cjnIpxRipFilterNetStart.name: cjnIpxRipFilterNetStart
cjnIpxRipFilterNetStart.description: The first IPX network number in the range which this filter matches.

cjnIpxRipFilterNetEnd.name: cjnIpxRipFilterNetEnd
cjnIpxRipFilterNetEnd.description: The last IPX network number in the range which this filter matches.

cjnIpxRipFilterDirection.name: cjnIpxRipFilterDirection
cjnIpxRipFilterDirection.description: The direction of IPX RIP packets to which this filter applies. Inbound applies the filter only to RIP packets received on the interface. Outbound applies the filter only to RIP packets sent on the interface. Both applies the filter to RIP packets sent and received on the interface.

cjnIpxRipFilterAction.name: cjnIpxRipFilterAction
cjnIpxRipFilterAction.description: The action to take if this filter matches an IPX RIP entry. Filter causes the RIP entry to be ignored in received RIP packets or suppressed in sent RIP packets. Allow causes the RIP entry to be accepted in received RIP packets or advertised in sent RIP packets.

cjnIpxRipFilterTicks.name: cjnIpxRipFilterTicks
cjnIpxRipFilterTicks.description: Used to override the delay, in ticks, to reach the IPX network specified in the RIP entry.

cjnIpxRipFilterHops.name: cjnIpxRipFilterHops
cjnIpxRipFilterHops.description: Used to override the hops to reach the IPX network specified in the RIP entry.

cjnIpxRipIfTable.name: cjnIpxRipIfTable
cjnIpxRipIfTable.description: A list of Cajun IPX RIP interface entries.

cjnIpxRipIfEntry.name: cjnIpxRipIfEntry
cjnIpxRipIfEntry.description: A Cajun IPX RIP interface instance.

cjnIpxRipIfRowStatus.name: cjnIpxRipIfRowStatus
cjnIpxRipIfRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

cjnIpxRipIfInterpacketGap.name: cjnIpxRipIfInterpacketGap
cjnIpxRipIfInterpacketGap.description: If set to enable(1), IPX RIP packets from periodic advertisements are sent with an interpacket gap of 55 milliseconds. If set to disable(2), no interpacket gap is used.

cjnIpxRipIfUseMaximumPacketSize.name: cjnIpxRipIfUseMaximumPacketSize
cjnIpxRipIfUseMaximumPacketSize.description: If set to enable(1), IPX RIP packets will contain as many entries as will fit in the maximum packet size allowable on the interface given the configured encapsulation type. If set to disable(2), IPX RIP packets will contain at most 50 entries.

cjnIpxRipIfUpdateInterval.name: cjnIpxRipIfUpdateInterval
cjnIpxRipIfUpdateInterval.description: The RIP periodic update interval, in seconds.

cjnIpxRipIfAgeMultiplier.name: cjnIpxRipIfAgeMultiplier
cjnIpxRipIfAgeMultiplier.description: The holding multiplier for information received in RIP updates. RIP information will be kept for the number of seconds indicated by the cjnIpxRipIfUpdateInterval multiplied by the cjnIpxRipIfAgeMultiplier.

cjnIpxRipIfTriggeredUpdates.name: cjnIpxRipIfTriggeredUpdates
cjnIpxRipIfTriggeredUpdates.description: Specified whether or not RIP updates are immediately sent on the interface in response to changes in the routing table.

cjnIpxRipIfAdvertiseDefaultRouteOnly.name: cjnIpxRipIfAdvertiseDefaultRouteOnly
cjnIpxRipIfAdvertiseDefaultRouteOnly.description: Specifies whether or not ONLY the default route (FFFFFFFE) is advertised in RIP updates sent on the interface.

cjnIpxRipIfMode.name: cjnIpxRipIfMode
cjnIpxRipIfMode.description: The handling of RIP packets on the interface. If set to talk(1), RIP packets may be sent on the interface but not received. If set to listen(2), RIP packets may be received but not sent. If set to both(3), RIP packets may be sent and received.

cjnIpxRipIfStatTable.name: cjnIpxRipIfStatTable
cjnIpxRipIfStatTable.description: A list of Cajun IPX RIP interface statistics entries.

cjnIpxRipIfStatEntry.name: cjnIpxRipIfStatEntry
cjnIpxRipIfStatEntry.description: A Cajun IPX RIP interface statistics instance.

cjnIpxRipIfStatTriggeredUpdatesSent.name: cjnIpxRipIfStatTriggeredUpdatesSent
cjnIpxRipIfStatTriggeredUpdatesSent.description: The number of RIP triggered updates sent on the interface.

cjnIpxRipIfStatPeriodicUpdatesSent.name: cjnIpxRipIfStatPeriodicUpdatesSent
cjnIpxRipIfStatPeriodicUpdatesSent.description: The number of periodic RIP updates sent on the interface.

cjnIpxRipIfStatUpdatesReceived.name: cjnIpxRipIfStatUpdatesReceived
cjnIpxRipIfStatUpdatesReceived.description: The number of RIP updates received on the interface.

cjnIpxRipIfStatRequestsReceived.name: cjnIpxRipIfStatRequestsReceived
cjnIpxRipIfStatRequestsReceived.description: The number of RIP requests received on the interface.

cjnIpxRipIfStatBadPacketsReceived.name: cjnIpxRipIfStatBadPacketsReceived
cjnIpxRipIfStatBadPacketsReceived.description: The number of incorrectly formatted RIP packets received on the interface.

cjnIpxRipIfStatsReset.name: cjnIpxRipIfStatsReset
cjnIpxRipIfStatsReset.description: When set to the value enable (1) all IPX RIP statistics for this interface are reset to zero after which the value of this MIB object returns to disable(2).
